<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cadmiumDissolved> skos:definition "Cadmium is a chemical element with symbol Cd and atomic number 48. This soft, bluish-white metal is chemically similar to the two other stable metals in group 12, zinc and mercury. Like zinc, it demonstrates oxidation state +2 in most of its compounds, and like mercury, it has a lower melting point than the transition metals in groups 3 through 11. Cadmium and its congeners in group 12 are often not considered transition metals, in that they do not have partly filled d or f electron shells in the elemental or common oxidation states. The average concentration of cadmium in Earth's crust is between 0.1 and 0.5 parts per million (ppm).",
        "Dissolved Cadmium. For chemical terms, \"dissolved\" indicates a filtered sample." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cadmium" ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV.",
        "Wikipedia" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:note "Added to support Critical Zone Observatory (CZO) data use cases. " ;
    skos:prefLabel "Cadmium, dissolved" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cadmiumDistributionCoefficient> skos:definition "Ratio of concentrations of cadmium in two phases in equilibrium with each other. Phases must be specified." ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV." ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Cadmium, distribution coefficient" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cadmiumParticulate> skos:definition "Particulate cadmium (Cd) in suspension" ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV." ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Cadmium, particulate" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cadmiumTotal> skos:definition "Total Cadmium (Cd). For chemical terms, \"total\" indciates an unfiltered sample." ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV." ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
