<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cristobalite> skos:definition "The mineral cristobalite is a high-temperature polymorph of silica, meaning that it has the same chemical formula as quartz, SiO2, but a distinct crystal structure." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cristobalite" ;
    skos:historyNote "Wikipedia" ;
