<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/curvature> skos:definition "Curvature of a DEM measures the shape or curvature of the slope. A part of a surface can be concave or convex; you can tell that by looking at the curvature value. The curvature is calculated by computing the second derivative of the surface." ;
    skos:exactMatch "http://desktop.arcgis.com/en/arcmap/10.3/manage-data/raster-and-images/curvature-function.htm" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:note "Added to support Critical Zone Observatory (CZO) data use cases. " ;
    skos:prefLabel "Curvature" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cuscutaSppCoverage> skos:definition "Areal coverage of the plant Cuscuta spp." ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV." ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Cuscuta spp. coverage" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/cyclohexane> skos:definition "Cyclohexane (C6H6Cl6)" ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV." ;
