<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/fluorescenceXRay> skos:definition "X-ray fluorescence (XRF) is the emission of characteristic \"secondary\" (or fluorescent) X-rays from a material that has been excited by bombarding with high-energy X-rays or gamma rays." ;
