<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/indium> skos:definition "Indium is a chemical element with symbol In and atomic number 49. It is a post-transition metal that makes up 0.21 parts per million of the Earth's crust. Very soft and malleable, indium has a melting point higher than sodium and gallium, but lower than lithium and tin." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indium" ;
    skos:historyNote "Wikipedia" ;
