<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/nacrite> skos:definition "Nacrite Al2Si2O5(OH)4 is a clay mineral that is polymorphous (or polytypic) with kaolinite. It crystallizes in the monoclinic system. X-ray diffraction analysis is required for positive identification. Nacrite was first described in 1807 for an occurrence in Saxony, Germany. The name is from nacre in reference to the mother of pearl luster of nacrite masses." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nacrite" ;
    skos:historyNote "Wikipedia" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:note "Added to support Critical Zone Observatory (CZO) data use cases. " ;
    skos:prefLabel "Nacrite" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/neodymium> skos:definition "Neodymium is a chemical element with symbol Nd and atomic number 60. It is a soft silvery metal that tarnishes in air. Neodymium was discovered in 1885 by the Austrian chemist Carl Auer von Welsbach." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neodymium" ;
    skos:historyNote "Wikipedia" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:note "Added to support Critical Zone Observatory (CZO) data use cases. " ;
    skos:prefLabel "Neodymium" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/neodymiumDissolved> skos:definition "Dissolved Neodymium (Nd). \"Dissolved \" indicates a the measurement was made on a filtered sample." ;
