<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/thorium> skos:definition "Thorium (Th)",
        "Thorium is a weakly radioactive metallic chemical element with symbol Th and atomic number 90. Thorium is silvery and tarnishes black when it is exposed to air, forming thorium dioxide; it is moderately hard, malleable, and has a high melting point." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thorium" ;
    skos:historyNote "Originally from the CUAHSI HIS VariableNameCV.  See: http://his.cuahsi.org/mastercvreg/edit_cv11.aspx?tbl=VariableNameCV.",
        "Wikipedia" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:note "Added to support Critical Zone Observatory (CZO) data use cases. " ;
    skos:prefLabel "Thorium" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

