<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/titaniumDioxide> skos:definition """Titanium dioxide, also known as titanium(IV) oxide or titania, is the naturally occurring oxide of titanium, chemical formula TiO
 2. When used as a pigment, it is called titanium white, Pigment White 6 (PW6), or CI 77891.""" ;
