<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/topographicWetnessIndex> skos:definition "Topographic wetness index (TWI), also known as the compound topographic index (CTI), is a steady state wetness index. It is commonly used to quantify topographic control on hydrological processes." ;
    skos:exactMatch "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topographic_wetness_index" ;
