<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/ultravioletRadiationDose> ns3:category "Biota" ;
    skos:definition "A measure of the ability of ultraviolet radiation, as a function of wavelength, to produce just perceptible erythema in human skin." ;
    skos:historyNote "See http://support.bentham.co.uk/support/solutions/articles/5000619299-erythemal-radiant-exposure-and-uv-index" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Ultraviolet Radiation Dose" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/ultravioletRadiationIndex> ns3:category "Biota" ;
    skos:definition "The global solar UV index (UVI) was developed as an easy-to-understand measure of biologically effective UV radiation with a view to promote public awareness of the risks of UV radiation exposure and sun protection. In the initial work done on UVI in Canada, a typical midday summer erythemal irradiance of 250 mW.m-2 was found leading to the (arbitrary) definition of one UV index equal to an erythemally weighted irradiance of 25 mW.m-2. This gives a typical range of UVI 0 to 11+." ;
    skos:historyNote "See http://support.bentham.co.uk/support/solutions/articles/5000619299-erythemal-radiant-exposure-and-uv-index" ;
    skos:inScheme <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Ultraviolet Radation Index" ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename> .

