<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/vermiculite> skos:definition "Vermiculite is a hydrous phyllosilicate mineral. It undergoes significant expansion when heated. Exfoliation occurs when the mineral is heated sufficiently, and the effect is routinely produced in commercial furnaces." ;
