    skos:note "The unit \"µmho\" (or \"umho\") is an obsolete unit of electrical conductance. It is the reciprocal of the ohm (the unit of electrical resistance), and is equivalent to the modern unit Siemens (S). Specifically, 1 µmho = 1 µS (microsiemens). While \"mho\" (and its multiples like \"µmho\") is no longer an accepted SI unit, it is sometimes still encountered in older literature or on some equipment, according to www.sizes.com"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "CONDUCTIVITY"@en .

