<https://water.sec.usace.army.mil/cda/reporting/projects#ConservationStorage> rdfs:seeAlso "https://www.spk-wc.usace.army.mil/glossary.html"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    skos:broadMatch <http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/reservoirStorage> ;
    skos:broader <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#c_b0cbf49d> ;
    skos:definition "[from Google AI] the volume of water in a reservoir that is reserved for non-flood control purposes. This storage space, typically located below the Top of Conservation Pool (TCP), can be used for purposes like water supply, recreation, and environmental flows. The TCP is a critical elevation that defines the boundary between flood control storage and conservation storage"@en ;
    skos:editorialNote "ac-ft"@en ;
    skos:hiddenLabel "Conservation Storage"@en ;
    skos:inScheme <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_3e018a2a> ;
    skos:note "Conservation storage is available for various purposes like water supply, recreation, and environment flows. "@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Conservation Storage"@en .

