    skos:note "This group contains the RISE parameters from parameterGroupId 20: Microbiological Analytes. It includes parameters that measure the presence, concentration, or activity of microorganisms in water, such as bacteria, viruses, and other microbial indicators. These variables are commonly used to assess water quality, contamination, and potential health risks, and are therefore closely related to water quality."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Microbiological Analytes"@en ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_8257cf0e> .

