<http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#c_7f5824ac> skos:inScheme <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_8257cf0e> ;
    skos:note "The Irradiance group comprises variables describing solar and terrestrial radiation fluxes at the land surface. It includes measurements of incoming radiation (e.g., shortwave, longwave, and PAR), reflected and emitted energy, and derived quantities such as net solar radiation and ground heat flux. Some RISE variables included in this group, such as Solar Radiation, may also be classified under Weather Data (parameterGroupId: 3)."@en,
        "This group comprises parameters describing inorganic chemical constituents in water, including dissolved ions, nutrients, and trace metals. It contains RISE parameters from parameterGroupId 18: Inorganic Analytes."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Irradiance"@en ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_8257cf0e> .

<http://vocabulary.odm2.org/variablename/conceptScheme_7c70597b> skos:prefLabel "IOW Variable Classifications"@en .

<http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#c_24c3807d> skos:inScheme <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_8257cf0e> ;
    skos:note "This group contains the RISE parameters from parameterGroupId 21: Physical Analytes. It includes parameters that describe the physical and general chemical properties of water, such as alkalinity, hardness, and other bulk characteristics. These variables are commonly used to assess overall water quality and the chemical balance of aquatic systems."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Physical Analytes"@en ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_8257cf0e> .

<https://data.usbr.gov/rise/api/parameter-group/18> skos:broader <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#c_ee622e19> ;
