    skos:note "This group contains the RISE parameters from parameterGroupId 31: Macrobiological Characteristics. This group includes parameters that describe the presence, abundance, or observed counts of macroscopic organisms (e.g., fish, invertebrates, or other aquatic species). These variables typically represent biological monitoring data, such as species counts, population observations, or migration metrics, often collected over a defined time interval."@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Macrobiological Characteristics"@en ;
    skos:topConceptOf <http://lincolninst.edu/cgs/vocabularies/usbr#conceptScheme_8257cf0e> .

